article.headline: Monmouth, N.J. 63, St. Francis, Pa. 53
article.story: LORETTO, Pa. -- Travis Taylor scored 20 points and Monmouth (N.J.) used a late surge to defeat Saint Francis (Pa.) 63-53 on Thursday night and win its fifth straight game. The Hawks (8-9, 4-1 Northeast Conference) broke a tie at 28 with a 15-2 spurt and led 43-30 with 10:58 to go. The game was tied six times in the first half before Justin Sofman's 3-pointer gave Monmouth a 22-21 lead at the break. The Hawks scored 23 points off 20 Red Flash turnovers. Monmouth shot only 35.7 percent from the field in the first half (10-for-28), but improved to 56.5 percent (13-for-23) in the second to finish at 45.1 percent (23-for-51). Saint Francis shot 37.2 percent (16-for-43) for the game. Sofman finished with 15 points for the Hawks and Whitney Coleman added 13. Anthony Ervin scored 12 points for the Red Flash (4-12, 2-3) and Sorena Orandi and Umar Shannon added 11 points apiece.
